    {
      "_id": "uS98HfKqTgAefSsN",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
      "name": "Devour Life",
      "sort": 1000000,
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The baykok is adjacent to a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.6uEgoh53GbXuHpTF]{Paralyzed}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.VcDeM8A5oI6VqhbM]{Restrained}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.fBnFDH2MTzgFijKf]{Unconscious} living humanoid.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The baykok touches the target and devours part of its life force. The target must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:26] save or be afflicted with the baykok's wasting curse. If the target fails and wasn't already affected by the wasting curse, the baykok gains [[/r 20 #Temporary Hit Points]]{20 temporary Hit Points} that last for 1 hour.</p>"
        },
